<br>
First off, when you first made your mage, when you were reading that little blurb about your hometown, perhaps you saw that the class/race combination you chose was of Moderate to Hard difficulty..<br>
<br>
Perhaps you have also seen that a barbarian warrior is of Low difficulty...<br>
<br>
Obviously, mages are a challenge, and a certain type of person enjoys playing the game in a more difficult setting (call it masochism, call it whatever you like)<br>
<br>
However, there are certain spots/times that a mage is quite useful.. IE, the smart group in crypt has a mage, as well as a rogue.. why?  because when the evaccer has to log, you don't have to leave.. Same goes for Every Single xp camp that you cant walk to from the zone without fighting.. If people don't see that, then they are fans of having to fight from the zoneline all over again, and hope someone else doesn't steal the camp.<br>
<br>
AE grouping gets brought up constantly... And it is a viable solution.. are you and the 2 wizards next to you LFG?  find one of the twink chanters that switched from mages, grab a cleric (prolly also a former mage) and a pally (go figure, also LFG), and you have a group to make the &quot;standard&quot; group get pissed cause there's nothing for them to pull.  Hell, if you get lucky, they'll offer to pull for you  (&quot;if you don't give us pulls, I'm gonna train you&quot;... I've had people tell me that)<br>
<br>
Still can't find a group?  go find an sk, they're usually soloing too... there, now you have a partner, whose strengths happen to be where your weaknesses are.<br>
<br>
If you're trying to get into stereotypical 'perfect' groups, you're competing against every other non-Holy Trinity class for that one coveted spot... so don't bother, it's a waste of your time.<br>
<br>
Mages are a jack of all trades class.. you Can crowd control, on a limited basis.. you Can mana battery a group, just takes effort, you Can be an offensive presence in a group..<br>
<br>
What a magician Can't do is convince A_Warrior_LFG_001 that the world continues outside of velks or seb or ME... that there is an entire world (plus a moon) in between those port spots, and that there are things to kill there, too.. <br>
<br>
So find yourself a partner, make yourself a group, make it as unorthadox as possible, you'd be surprised.<br>
<br>
If you're not willing to leave those zones, then please do make a different class twink, and allow the other players to know who the serious mage players are.<br>
<br>
What it all comes down to is fun.. if you're not having fun, because you &lt;u&gt; perceive &lt;/u&gt; that nobody likes mages, don't play your mage anymore.. If you continue playing your mage simply because you spent so much time on him, then play a different game.<br>
<br>
Maephestos Vanhausen<br>
57 Conjurer<br>
