1 - Monks add monks to your damage dealer list.<br>
2 - seriously you would consider taking a mage over a warrior that do 30% 40% less damage????? <br>
The warrior can tank, the warrior won't brake mezs, tha warrior wont train you, if the mage were to train you you would loose far more than the additional XP you gained with his additional damages.<br>
<br>
Now let us say that you have a group of 5 that are trying to make XP. The only thing they need is XP (not help their local fellow magician that has trouble to make XP) so they will try to fill the last slot with the class that will give them the best XP.<br>
And let us say that you have this group <br>
1 monk<br>
1 ench<br>
1 ranger<br>
1 war <br>
1 Cleric<br>
<br>
To simplify the things let us say that the monk the warrior and the ranger are dealing the same amout of damage that is 40% less than a mage. Those 3 will deal 180% the damage of a mage, add a new warrior and you have 240% the damage of a mage and an additional tank (that can always help), add a mage and you have 280% the damage of a mage. That is 16% damage increase in your group. <br>
Sincerely this group does not need a mage, it needs a rogue, another monk, a wizard maybe for evac. If those person are supersitious and are afraid to be trained they will even choose a warrior instead of a mage. If they think that an additional warrior can save their but in case of catastrophy better than a mage they will pick another warrior. <br>
As for the pet saving groups by tanking. I don't think that players that don't play pet class think of pets that way, they (rightfully) think of pets as liability. I play my magician well however, in full groups, the pet means more often trouble than he is saving the group.<br>
<br>
However at 60 with water pet, rod2 and clarity2 or Kodiacs, regrowth and  12 AA points, the mellees that are below 54 generally just cannot compete with me as damage output, I have the real feeling that i can deal 2 or 3 times their damage. But then again a level 60 rogue will make me feel a parasite in the group, just picking xp while doing very little damage.<br>
